{
  "body": "Item context is listed among operators in [S03](https://github.com/perl6/specs/blob/master/S03-operators.pod), but does not appear to be in the Language/operators documentation, nor listed on the docs site in the list of Routines.\n\nThe phrase \"item context\" is mentioned in only two places and not well explained in either:\n\n```\ndoc/Language/5to6-perlop.pod\n73:named variable, you can use item context, like so: C<$aref = item(@array)>\n\ndoc/Language/faq.pod\n300:on an expression, and item context (not flattening) with C<$( ... )>\n```\n",
